nl.tudelft.simulation.dsol.formalisms.flow

Class Generator<A extends java.lang.Comparable<A>,R extends java.lang.Number & java.lang.Comparable<R>,T extends SimTime<A,R,T>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • nl.tudelft.simulation.event.EventProducer
      • nl.tudelft.simulation.dsol.formalisms.flow.Station<A,R,T>
        • nl.tudelft.simulation.dsol.formalisms.flow.Generator<A,R,T>
  • Type Parameters:
    A - the absolute storage type for the simulation time, e.g. Calendar, Duration, or Double.
    R - the relative type for time storage, e.g. Long for the Calendar. For most non-calendar types, the absolute and relative types are the same.
    T - the extended type itself to be able to implement a comparator on the simulation time.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, StationInterface, nl.tudelft.simulation.event.EventProducerInterface

    • Constructor Detail

      • Generator

        public Generator(DEVSSimulatorInterface<A,R,T> simulator,
                 java.lang.Class<?> myClass,
                 java.lang.Object[] constructorArguments)
          throws SimRuntimeException
        constructs a new generator for objects in a simulation. Constructed objects are sent to the 'destination' of the Generator when a destination has been indicated with the setDestination method. This constructor has a maximum number of entities generated, which results in stopping the generator when the maximum number of entities has been reached.
        Parameters:
        simulator - is the on which the construction of the objects must be scheduled.
        myClass - is the class of which entities are created
        constructorArguments - are the parameters for the constructor of myClass. of arguments. constructorArgument[n]=new Integer(12) may have constructorArgumentClasses[n]=int.class;
        Throws:
        SimRuntimeException - on constructor invocation.
